OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FThe 'burning prisons'      
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ffuelled by fast fashion    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Chantrea drags an electric fan the size
OL,6, of a large door into the airless       
OL,7, chamber where she works every day.     
OL,9,FIt is her only respite from the heat   
OL,10,Finside the brick kiln that looks more  
OL,11,Flike a dimly-lit tomb.                 
OL,13,F"It's like working inside a burning    
OL,14,Fprison," the 47-year-old says as she   
OL,15,Fstacks the dried bricks, which will be 
OL,16,Fmoved to a warehouse. "I have asked the
OL,17,Fowners to provide us with more fans.   
OL,18,FBut they won't because it will cost    
OL,19,Fmore money."                           
